<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Learning on Learnings</title><link>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/tags/learning/</link><description>Recent content in Learning on Learnings</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Sat, 11 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/tags/learning/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Claude Code CLI Orchestration via --print Mode</title><link>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/claude-code-cli-orchestration/</link><pubDate>Sat, 11 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/claude-code-cli-orchestration/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Using nanobot to drive Claude Code programmatically as a coding sub-agent.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="problem"&gt;Problem&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Claude Code is a powerful coding agent, but it runs as an interactive REPL. We needed a way for nanobot (running on Telegram) to delegate coding tasks to Claude Code and get results back — without human interaction at the terminal.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="solution---print-mode"&gt;Solution: &lt;code&gt;--print&lt;/code&gt; Mode&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Claude Code&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;-p&lt;/code&gt; flag runs a single non-interactive turn:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;claude -p &lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c"&gt;&amp;#34;implement feature X&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; --output-format text &lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; --max-turns &lt;span style="color:#bd93f9"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; --allowedTools &lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c"&gt;&amp;#34;Write,Edit,Bash&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Key flags:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Tool Call Timeouts</title><link>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/tool-call-timeouts/</link><pubDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/tool-call-timeouts/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Atomic File Writes</title><link>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/atomic-file-writes/</link><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/atomic-file-writes/</guid><description/></item><item><title>launchd Service Management</title><link>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/launchd-service-management/</link><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/launchd-service-management/</guid><description/></item><item><title>LLM Model Fallback Chains</title><link>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/llm-model-fallback-chains/</link><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/llm-model-fallback-chains/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Resilient JSONL Loading</title><link>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/resilient-jsonl-loading/</link><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/resilient-jsonl-loading/</guid><description/></item><item><title>SSRF Whitelisting Localhost</title><link>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/ssrf-whitelisting-localhost/</link><pubDate>Wed, 08 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/ssrf-whitelisting-localhost/</guid><description/></item></channel></rss>